The paper deals with the containment problem under homothetics, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces new radii and derives sharp inequalities, which involve mathematical analysis and optimization, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses core-sets, which are a common topic in machine learning and data analysis, making cs.MG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves mathematical inequalities and optimization, which are common in theoretical computer science, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category as well.
